MS Dos Prompt
------
ROBOCOPY T:\PL\AFTER\PL C:\tst *.cfg *.pl /E     --This will copy all the directory tree under T:\PL\AFTER\PL along with only .cfg and .pl files in all the sub folders to c:\tst

findstr /CMS "HOLDINGSRPT" *

findstr /M /S /C:"SELECT SUM(NVL(TCAE.DIV_AMT,0)) FROM ESTAR_TEMP_CORP_ACT_ENT TCAE WHERE" *  -- This will search for string in double quotes irespcetive of whats present before and after the sting. You can test this command on directory c:\new folder. Aslo, this is case sensitive search

Findstr /?
FINDSTR [/B] [/E] [/L] [/R] [/S] [/I] [/X] [/V] [/N] [/M] [/O] [/P] [/F:file]
        [/C:string] [/G:file] [/D:dir list] [/A:color attributes] [/OFF[LINE]]
        ...
        ...
        ...